s Science and Engineering, McGraw-Hill,&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</p>
<p style=3D"text-align:justify">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; First Indian Edition, Ne=
w Delhi, 1996.<strong></strong><span style=3D"font-size:12pt"></span></p>
<p style=3D"text-align:justify"><span style=3D"font-size:12pt">2. M. R. Sri=
nivasan: Applied Solid State Physics: A Textbook of Materials Science,</spa=
n></p>
<p style=3D"text-align:justify"><span style=3D"font-size:12pt">&nbsp; &nbsp=
